To generate an automatic Table of Contents (TOC) in a LATEX document, you can use the `\tableofcontents` command placed after the abstract and before the main body content:

```
% LaTeX code for generating a TOC
\documentclass{article}

\begin{document}
    \maketitle
    \abstract

    % Automatic Table of Contents using 'tocloft' package
    \usepackage[toc]{tocloft}  
    \renewcommand{\cftbeforetoctitle}{\hfill\large Table of Contents\hfill\par\medskip}
    \setcounter{tocdepth}{3}      
    \tableofcontents        

    \chapter{Introduction}
    ...

    \section{Section 1}
    ...

    \subsection{Sub-Section 1}
    ...

    \subsubsection{Sub-Sub-Section 1}
    ...

    \paragraph{Paragraph 1}
    ...

    \subparagraph{Sub-Paragraph 1}
    ...

    % End of LaTeX code
```

In this example, we first import the `tocloft` package to customize the appearance of our TOC. Then, we define the title format with the `\renewcommand` command and set the depth level of sectioning elements that will appear in the TOC using the `\setcounter` command. Finally, we add the `\tableofcontents` command just after the chapter or section headings where you want to display the TOC. This will create a fully functional and formatted TOC based on the structure of the document.

